For addition I can&#x27;t either, but you could use it to overload multiplication of two (mathematical) vectors to a dot-product<p><pre><code>  impl Mul for Vec2{
    type Output = double;
    fn mul(self, other: Vec2) -> Double {
      self.0*other.0+self.1*other.1)
    }
  }
</code></pre>
Although I must admit I&#x27;m not (yet) sure why you need to explicitly state the output <i>and</i> define it for the function. But I have only just started with Rust.
